chatgpt_solution: First we simplify $\left( \frac{1}{2k} \right)^{-2}$: $$\left( \frac{1}{2k} \right)^{-2} = \left( \frac{1}{2k} \right)^2 = \frac{1}{(2k)^2} = \frac{1}{4k^2}.$$Thus we have $$\left( \frac{1}{2k} \right)^{-2} \cdot (-k)^3 = \frac{1}{4k^2} \cdot (-k)^3 = \frac{-k^3}{4k^2}.$$Simplifying the fraction in $\frac{-k^3}{4k^2}$ gives $\boxed{-\frac{k^3}{4k^2}}.$
